      <hedline>
        <hl1>ITALIAN BROOKLYN</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Patricia Lobosco letter says Danielle Pergament's May 20 travel article on Palermo, Italy, reminded her of her childhood in Bensonhurst, Brooklyn</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: The ''abbanniata'' described in Danielle Pergament's ''Sicily; In Palermo, Life Vibrates in a Fading Market (Journeys, May 20) was a daily part of my experience as a little girl growing up in Bensonhurst, Brooklyn. Although the fruit stands still stretch from 23rd Avenue to Bay Parkway along 86th Street, the tradition is gone, along with the many Italian immigrants who once predominated. Thanks for putting a name on a forgotten memory.</p>
        <p>Patricia Lobosco  Brooklyn, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
